26/05/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- The International Atomic Energy Agency announced on Tuesday (25 May) that it would provide expert advice and technical assistance to detect and protect against the use of radioactive materials during the Summer Olympics. 
The Czech Defence Ministry, meanwhile, offered to train 60 Greek soldiers in chemical decontamination techniques.
Jacques Rogge, president of the International Olympic Committee (IOC), said Tuesday he believes Greece will be ready to host the Games, which open on 13 August. 
He says IOC experts are convinced there is enough time to complete all remaining work. 
(AFP, Reuters, ANA, CNA, Reuters - 25/05/04)
